ARGUMENT

| Step | Hyp | Ref | Expression |
|---|---|---|---|

| 1 |  | #P_axpre-lttrn | |- ( ( A e. RR /\ B e. RR /\ C e. RR ) -> ( ( A <RR B /\ B <RR C ) -> A <RR C ) ) |
| 2 |  | #P_ltxrlt | |- ( ( A e. RR /\ B e. RR ) -> ( A < B <-> A <RR B ) ) |
| 3 | 2 | #P_3adant3 | |- ( ( A e. RR /\ B e. RR /\ C e. RR ) -> ( A < B <-> A <RR B ) ) |
| 4 |  | #P_ltxrlt | |- ( ( B e. RR /\ C e. RR ) -> ( B < C <-> B <RR C ) ) |
| 5 | 4 | #P_3adant1 | |- ( ( A e. RR /\ B e. RR /\ C e. RR ) -> ( B < C <-> B <RR C ) ) |
| 6 | 3, 5 | #P_anbi12d | |- ( ( A e. RR /\ B e. RR /\ C e. RR ) -> ( ( A < B /\ B < C ) <-> ( A <RR B /\ B <RR C ) ) ) |
| 7 |  | #P_ltxrlt | |- ( ( A e. RR /\ C e. RR ) -> ( A < C <-> A <RR C ) ) |
| 8 | 7 | #P_3adant2 | |- ( ( A e. RR /\ B e. RR /\ C e. RR ) -> ( A < C <-> A <RR C ) ) |
| 9 | 1, 6, 8 | #P_3imtr4d | |- ( ( A e. RR /\ B e. RR /\ C e. RR ) -> ( ( A < B /\ B < C ) -> A < C ) ) |
\
 Ordering on reals is transitive.  Axiom for real and complex numbers, derived from set theory.  This restates ~ ax-pre-lttrn with ordering on the extended reals.  New proofs should use ~ lttr instead for naming consistency.  (New usage is discouraged.)  (Contributed by NM, 13-Oct-2005.)
